The Clay MCP server is an integration that allows AI assistants to interact with your Clay relationship intelligence data [1][2]. You can connect via Clay's official URL (https://mcp.clay.earth/mcp) by following the guided login flow in your client, or via Smithery [3][4][5]. Alternatively, you can configure it locally in your config file using npx [6][7]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "clay-mcp": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@clayhq/clay-mcp@latest"],
      "env": {
        "CLAY_API_KEY": "YOUR_CLAY_API_KEY"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

It supports features like searching contacts, managing groups, retrieving notes and calendar events, and adding new entries [3][6].
